Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and quarter @button mushrooms{8%ounce}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2%unit}, separating whites from greens. Dice @Roma tomato{1%unit}.

== Garlicky Panko ==

Melt 1 TBSP @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}; cook, stirring, until golden and toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later). Cook until just fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

== Mushroom Gnocchi ==

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and a pinch of salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Reduce heat to medium.

Once mushrooms are browned and tender, add @gnocchi{8.8%ounce} to #pot{} of boiling water. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}, then drain.

Stir 1 TBSP @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings), scallion whites, and remaining garlic powder into pan with mushrooms. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in 1⁄3 cup water (½ cup for 4), @mushroom stock concentrate{1%unit}, @PHILADELPHIA® cream cheese{4%tablespoon}, and half the @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} (save the rest for serving). Cook, stirring, until combined and creamy, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Stir in tomato, another 1 TBSP @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4), and @truffle zest{2%g} to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

Stir drained gnocchi into pan with sauce until thoroughly coated.

> TIP: If needed, add water a splash at a time until gnocchi is coated in a creamy sauce.

Divide between #bowls{}; top with scallion greens and remaining Parmesan. Sprinkle with as much garlicky panko as you like and serve.